<b>Amplification test results - </b>1/23/02 3:02:32 PM<br>~ <b>Kocho Divah</b><blockquote>Tested at level 57 after the Amplification bug fix:<br><br>Sung<br>+ 15 INT/WIS<br><br>w/Epic<br>+26 INT/WIS<br><br>w/Amp<br>+28 INT/WIS<br><br>w/Epic + Amp<br>+40 INT/WIS</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>How to use for skills and combat - </b>11/29/01 4:17:55 PM<br>~ <b>Temperance</b><blockquote>Let me get the math out of the way, then comments:<br>When sung this adds points to both INT and WIS:<br><br>Bonus = 1 + ( Level / 4 )<br><br>So when we earn this at level 44 we get 1+(44/4)=1+(11)=12.<br>This means the cap of this song is at level 60 with +16.<br>44=+12 , 48=+13 , 52=+14 , 56=+15 , 60=+16 .<br><br>~~~~~~~~~~<br><br>Yes, I know, obvious application is to trade skills. And I USE IT. I am a master of the seven, nearing the threshold of Grand Master in four of them - Jewelcraft being one of them.<br>(I know you can only cross the line in one general tradeskill.)<br><br>I am assisting a halfling reach Tailoring 250 on Erollisi Marr. Once she receives an ENC buff for WIS and a SHM buff for DEX<br>she and I find a quiet corner and I twist Elegy(44) and CoB(1)<br>until the spells fade. It has helped her a great deal. I also have free combines for life from an ENC by helping him get his last 30 points in jewelry making.<br><br>Twisting this song for yourself will help also, but I have found I may only twist (stop1,start2) while using skills in containers I have in inventory (tailoring,feltching,jewelry,spit). I may no longer (or perhaps never could) twist while using community property (forge,barrel,wheel,kiln,oven,loom) in which case I have to fill the container, close it (risking theft), switch songs, re-open my trade book, re-open the container and press combine. Whew. Perhaps you might want to just stick with shammie buffs and sing Elegy by itself... Good thing the forge in the slum is never visited, or the one outside the Militia house.<br><br>~~~~~~~~~~<br><br>Okay, how to use this for battle with your group. Twist Elegy with your mana song of choice, making sure Elegy does not fade. While the Brain Boost is in effect your group's casters will have a slightly larger mana pool - fill it with mana song/ENC Clarity. The trick is to use this just before engagement so after they regen from buffing they may cast their initial wave of Nukes or DOTs or DS. When the Elegy fades and you are twisting for the Melee in your group your casters should still be at or near FM.<br><br>I do this mainly on major engagements. I don't explain it if they don't notice, but I am more then happy to tell them why if they ask. (Flee! not another lecture from temper! aaaa!)<br><br><br>Temperance Descant ~ Minstrel of Noble Heart ~ Erollisi Marr<br></blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Bigger Container, same mana - </b>10/17/01 3:26:09 PM<br>~ <b>Stacotto</b><blockquote>Let me preface this by saying that I do not have this song yet.  But I have played many a caster class.  In most all cases when a caster equips an item that increases the size of their mana pool it does so without adding the extra mana.  The extra mana still has to be generated through the use of mana song, spells, or medding.  So unless this song is played continuously then the extra mana capacity may not be realized by the caster.<br><br>Where I do see this song being usefull is in trade skill practice.  The higher intelligence will help level the skill faster and the higher wisdom will increase the number of successfull attempts.<br><br>Just my 2cp...<br><br>Stacotto Moderato<br>Terris Thule</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Trade skills - </b>10/15/01 1:06:49 AM<br>~ <b>Melodious</b><blockquote>The only usefullness for this song that i have found is if someone is doing a trade skill and needs an int/wis boost.  Or if i am doing a trade skill that i want to raise faster.  Using this song for just about anythign else is pointless.  there are better things that can be twisted in.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Hmm that may be valid - </b>8/24/01 2:05:58 PM<br>~ <b>Actus</b><blockquote>I have yet to test this, as I just got the song, but it seems that this may help a bit in terms of buffing...<br><br>If you play this, the casters mana pool will increase due to the stat bonus. Now, if they cast a buff, does the mana used come from this extra mana? If so, then when the song stops, the original mana pool is restored, leaving the caster FM. If not, then I agree, this song is rarely useful.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Only useful for skill increases - </b>5/11/01 5:10:58 PM<br>~ <b>Kaearia</b><blockquote>Contrary to the above comment, this song will not help during buffing.  Only the mana regeneration rate will affect how long it takes your party to buff.  The only time this song is really useful is when a party member is trying to increase skill.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
